## Key Difference vs PDF Module
PPT content is SLIDE-STRUCTURED not page-flow. Each slide is a self-contained 
unit with:
  - A title (explicit, not inferred from font size)
  - Bullet points (hierarchical, not paragraphs)
  - Speaker notes (highly valuable — often more detailed than slide text)
  - Visuals: charts, tables, images (need special handling)

Chunking strategy: slide = natural chunk boundary (not token count).
Token splitting is only fallback for abnormally dense slides.

