## Implementation Details

### ApachePptExtractor.java
Use Apache POI XMLSlideShow:

XMLSlideShow pptx = new XMLSlideShow(new FileInputStream(path.toFile()));

For each XSLFSlide:

1. TITLE: getPlaceholder(0) → getText() → slide title
   If null, try getPlaceholder(1) → first text shape → use as title

2. BULLET POINTS: iterate getShapes() → XSLFTextShape
   For each XSLFTextParagraph:
     - getIndentLevel() gives hierarchy (0 = top, 1 = sub-bullet, etc.)
     - Prefix with indent: "  ".repeat(indentLevel) + "• " + text
     - Skip shapes that are the title placeholder

3. SPEAKER NOTES: slide.getNotes()
   If not null → getNotesParagraph() → extract text
   Strip "Click to edit..." default placeholder text

4. TABLES: XSLFTable shape
   Iterate rows/cols → build markdown table string
   | col1 | col2 |
   |------|------|
   | val  | val  |

5. CHARTS: XSLFChart shape
   Extract: chart.getChartSeries() title if available
   Build string: "Chart: {title}, Type: {BAR|LINE|PIE}, 
                  Categories: {list}, Series: {list}"
   If chart metadata unavailable → "Chart present on slide {n}"

6. IMAGES: just set hasImages = true, no extraction

7. LAYOUT: slide.getSlideLayout().getType().name()

8. RAW TEXT: concat all above as fallback

Detect .ppt (legacy binary):
  If file extension is .ppt → throw UnsupportedOperationException with message:
  "Legacy .ppt format not supported. Please convert to .pptx first."

Close XMLSlideShow in finally block.

### SlideAwareChunker.java (default strategy)
One chunk per slide — slides are natural semantic units:

For each ExtractedSlide, assemble text in this order:
  1. "Title: {title}"
  2. Bullet points joined by \n (with indent preserved)
  3. Tables (each as markdown block)
  4. Chart descriptions
  5. If config.includeSpeakerNotes == true:
       "\n\n[Speaker Notes]\n{speakerNotes}"

Check token count via JTokkit:
  - If tokenCount <= config.chunkSize (default 512) → single PptChunk
  - If tokenCount > 512 → split: 
      Chunk A: title + bullets + tables (slide content)
      Chunk B: "[Speaker Notes - Slide {n}]\n" + speakerNotes
    Both chunks share same slideNumber, different chunkIndex

Tables and charts: always separate chunk with isTable=true if they push
slide over token limit.

After all chunks → set prevChunkId / nextChunkId linked list.

### DenseSlideChunker.java (fallback for text-heavy slides)
Used when a single slide body exceeds 512 tokens even without notes:
- Delegate bullet point text to RecursiveTokenChunker (reuse from pdf module)
- Each sub-chunk inherits slideNumber and slideTitle
- Prefix each sub-chunk: "[Slide {n} - Part {i}] {title}\n{text}"

### SlideContextEnricher.java
Inject ChatLanguageModel (same instance as PDF enricher):

Prompt per chunk:
"""
Presentation: {deckTitle}
Slide {slideNumber} of {totalSlides}: {slideTitle}
Slide content: {first 300 chars of chunk.text}

In one sentence (max 20 words), what is this slide communicating?
"""

Set chunk.enrichedText = "[Context: {response}]\n\n{chunk.text}"
On failure → fall back to raw text, log warning, never fail pipeline.

Special case: if slideTitle is non-null and chunk.text is short (< 100 tokens)
→ skip LLM call, use:
enrichedText = "[Slide {slideNumber}: {slideTitle}]\n\n{chunk.text}"

### PptIngestionPipeline.java
Constructor inject (same pattern as PDF pipeline):
- PptExtractor extractor
- PptChunker chunker
- ChunkEnricher enricher              // nullable
- EmbeddingStore<TextSegment> embeddingStore
- EmbeddingModel embeddingModel
- YourPersistenceService persistenceService

ingest(Path pptPath):
1. persistenceService.existsBySource() → skip if already processed
2. ExtractedPresentation deck = extractor.extract(pptPath)
3. List<PptChunk> chunks = chunker.chunk(deck)
4. If enricher != null → enrich each chunk
5. Embed → store in embeddingStore
6. persistenceService.saveChunks(chunks)
7. Return PipelineResult

ingestDirectory(Path dir):
- Glob *.pptx (warn and skip *.ppt files)
- Call ingest() per file
- Aggregate results

### PptCrawlerConfig.java
@Data
public class PptCrawlerConfig {
    private String chunkStrategy      = "slide";   // "slide" | "dense"
    private int chunkSize             = 512;
    private boolean includeSpeakerNotes = true;    // HIGH VALUE — keep true
    private boolean enableEnrichment  = true;
    private boolean recursiveScan     = false;
}

